"{\"uid\": \"rappler.com-sports-opening-ceremony-paris-olympics-2024\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"  SUMMARY  This is AI generated summarization, which may have errors.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 69, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 19, \"end\": 21, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 0.9999643832883607, \"rank\": 3.561797992219578e-05, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For context, always refer to the full article.\", \"from\": 70, \"to\": 116, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"SPECTACULAR.\", \"from\": 118, \"to\": 130, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Eiffel Tower is illuminated during the opening ceremony of the Paris 2024 Olympics.\", \"from\": 131, \"to\": 218, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Pawel Kopczynski/REUTERS  PARIS, France - French President Emmanuel Macron declared the Olympic Games open on Friday, July 26, after a soaking wet ceremony in which athletes were cheered by the crowd along the Seine River, dancers took to the roofs of Paris and Lady Gaga sang a French cabaret song.\", \"from\": 220, \"to\": 519, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 237, \"end\": 244, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"REUTERS\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}, {\"begin\": 253, \"end\": 259, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5012365867739817e-13, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 262, \"end\": 278, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French President\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_France\"}, {\"begin\": 279, \"end\": 294, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emmanuel Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}, {\"begin\": 472, \"end\": 477, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5860334755717507e-32, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 482, \"end\": 491, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lady Gaga\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\"}, {\"begin\": 499, \"end\": 505, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9953359198909087, \"rank\": 0.004627841915488241, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"France's three-time Olympic gold medalists Marie-Jose Perec and Teddy Riner then lit the Olympic cauldron, suspended on a hot-air balloon, before Canada's\\u00a0Celine Dion\\u00a0sang Edith Piaf's \\\"Hymn to Love,\\\" in her first public performance in years, drawing huge cheers from the crowd.\", \"from\": 521, \"to\": 799, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 521, \"end\": 527, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5012365867739817e-13, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 564, \"end\": 580, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie-Jos\\u00e9_P\\u00e9rec\", \"score\": 0.9999999999290594, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Marie-Jose Perec\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie-Jos\\u00e9_P\\u00e9rec\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie-Jos\\u00e9_P\\u00e9rec\"}, {\"begin\": 585, \"end\": 596, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Teddy_Riner\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Teddy Riner\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Teddy_Riner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Teddy_Riner\"}, {\"begin\": 667, \"end\": 673, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 0.999999910650335, \"rank\": 8.933854264455644e-08, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}, {\"begin\": 676, \"end\": 687, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.502849216849817e-53, \"text\": \"Celine Dion\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\"}, {\"begin\": 693, \"end\": 703, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00c9dith_Piaf\", \"score\": 0.9999999912251951, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Edith Piaf\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00c9dith_Piaf\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00c9dith_Piaf\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A fleet of barges took the competitors on a 6-kilometer stretch of the river alongside some of the French capital's most famous landmarks, as performers recreated some of the sports to be showcased in the Games on floating platforms.\", \"from\": 801, \"to\": 1034, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 900, \"end\": 906, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9953359198909087, \"rank\": 0.004627841915488241, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"More than 10,500 athletes will compete at the Olympics, 100 years since Paris last staged the Games.\", \"from\": 1036, \"to\": 1136, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1108, \"end\": 1113, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5860334755717507e-32, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Competition started on Wednesday and the first of the 329 gold medals will be awarded on Saturday, July 27.\", \"from\": 1137, \"to\": 1244, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was the first time that an opening ceremony has taken place outside a stadium, adding to the headaches for a vast security operation, just hours after a sabotage attack on the high-speed TGV rail network caused travel chaos across France.\", \"from\": 1246, \"to\": 1487, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1436, \"end\": 1439, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TGV\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"TGV\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TGV\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TGV\"}, {\"begin\": 1480, \"end\": 1486, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5012365867739817e-13, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I invite everybody: dream with us.\", \"from\": 1489, \"to\": 1524, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Like the Olympic athletes, be inspired with the joy that only sport can give us.\", \"from\": 1525, \"to\": 1605, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Let us celebrate this Olympic spirit of living in peace,\\\" International Olympics Committee president Thomas Bach said as the ceremony came to an end at the foot of the Eiffel Tower.\", \"from\": 1606, \"to\": 1787, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1664, \"end\": 1696, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympics Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 1707, \"end\": 1718, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Thomas Bach\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A giant plume of blue, white and red smoke, resembling the French flag, was sent high above a bridge over the Seine at the start of the ceremony as part of a show that included many postcard-like depictions of France, including a huge cancan line performed by Moulin Rouge dancers on the banks.\", \"from\": 1789, \"to\": 2083, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1848, \"end\": 1859, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French flag\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_France\"}, {\"begin\": 1899, \"end\": 1904, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2625200333453086e-22, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 1999, \"end\": 2005, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5012365867739817e-13, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 2049, \"end\": 2061, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moulin_Rouge\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.810804942762795e-46, \"text\": \"Moulin Rouge\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moulin_Rouge\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moulin_Rouge\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A more modern image of the country was on display when French-Malian pop star Aya Nakamura, the most-listened to French female singer in the world, sang some of her biggest hits, accompanied by the French Republican Guard's army choir.\", \"from\": 2085, \"to\": 2320, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2163, \"end\": 2175, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aya_Nakamura\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Aya Nakamura\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aya_Nakamura\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aya_Nakamura\"}, {\"begin\": 2198, \"end\": 2204, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9953359198909087, \"rank\": 0.004627841915488241, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 2283, \"end\": 2306, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republican_Guard_(France)\", \"score\": 0.9999999994734026, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French Republican Guard\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q176799\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republican_Guard_(France)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republican_Guard_(France)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nakamura's performance drew some of the ceremony's biggest cheers.\", \"from\": 2322, \"to\": 2388, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Rumors of her inclusion had sparked a row over French identity, with supporters saying said she represented the vibrancy of modern-day France while her detractors saying her music owes more to foreign influences than French.\", \"from\": 2389, \"to\": 2613, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2436, \"end\": 2442, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9953359198909087, \"rank\": 0.004627841915488241, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 2524, \"end\": 2530, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5012365867739817e-13, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 2606, \"end\": 2612, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9953359198909087, \"rank\": 0.004627841915488241, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A mix of French and international stars, including soccer great Zinedine Zidane, 14-time French Open champion Rafa Nadal, 23-time Grand Slam champion Serena Williams, athletics legend Carl Lewis, gymnastics great Nadia Comaneci, and three Paralympic athletes were among the last torchbearers before the cauldron was lit.\", \"from\": 2615, \"to\": 2935, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2624, \"end\": 2630, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9953359198909087, \"rank\": 0.004627841915488241, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 2679, \"end\": 2694, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zinedine_Zidane\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Zinedine Zidane\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q628099\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zinedine_Zidane\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zinedine_Zidane\"}, {\"begin\": 2725, \"end\": 2735, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rafa Nadal\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\"}, {\"begin\": 2765, \"end\": 2780, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serena_Williams\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Serena Williams\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serena_Williams\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serena_Williams\"}, {\"begin\": 2799, \"end\": 2809, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Carl Lewis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\"}, {\"begin\": 2828, \"end\": 2842, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nadia_Com\\u0103neci\", \"score\": 0.9999999839874364, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nadia Comaneci\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nadia_Com\\u0103neci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nadia_Com\\u0103neci\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It will blaze until the closing ceremony on August 11.\", \"from\": 2937, \"to\": 2991, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"While the celebration of French culture, fashion, and history was warmly cheered by many of the 300,000 spectators lining the river, hundreds were seen leaving early as the rain fell.\", \"from\": 2993, \"to\": 3176, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3018, \"end\": 3032, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French culture\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It was good other than the rain, it was nice, it was different, instead of being in a stadium being on the river, so that's always a good thing - interesting, unique,\\\" said Avid Pureval, 34, who came to the Games from Ohio.\", \"from\": 3178, \"to\": 3402, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3352, \"end\": 3356, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Avid_Technology\", \"score\": 0.9999999633946579, \"rank\": 3.175670561266897e-08, \"text\": \"Avid\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Avid_Technology\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Avid_Technology\"}, {\"begin\": 3397, \"end\": 3401, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ohio_River\", \"score\": 0.9960769859033962, \"rank\": 0.003938464744006325, \"text\": \"Ohio\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ohio_River\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ohio_River\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Once you are wet, it's fine,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 3404, \"to\": 3443, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Still, he was heading back to his hotel after the French boat passed.\", \"from\": 3444, \"to\": 3513, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3494, \"end\": 3500, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9953359198909087, \"rank\": 0.004627841915488241, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It would have been better with sun,\\\" said Josephine, from Paris, sitting beside her nine-year-old daughter and who paid 1,600 euros ($1,736) for her seat.\", \"from\": 3515, \"to\": 3670, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3574, \"end\": 3579, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5860334755717507e-32, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With many world leaders and VIPs present, the ceremony was protected by snipers on rooftops.\", \"from\": 3672, \"to\": 3764, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Seine's riverbed was swept for bombs, and Paris' airspace was closed.\", \"from\": 3765, \"to\": 3838, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3769, \"end\": 3774, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2625200333453086e-22, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 3811, \"end\": 3816, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5860334755717507e-32, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some 45,000 police and thousands of soldiers were deployed in a huge security operation in Paris for the ceremony.\", \"from\": 3840, \"to\": 3954, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3931, \"end\": 3936, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5860334755717507e-32, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Armed police patrolled along the river in inflatable boats as the armada made its passage along the Seine.\", \"from\": 3955, \"to\": 4061, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4055, \"end\": 4060, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2625200333453086e-22, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The torchbearer who will light the Olympic flame, their identity concealed, made appearances throughout the show.\", \"from\": 4063, \"to\": 4176, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At first seen jumping on the roofs of Paris, they were later filmed walking through the Louvre museum's empty corridors, in which - for the show - Leonardo da Vinci's Mona Lisa had supposedly disappeared.\", \"from\": 4177, \"to\": 4381, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4215, \"end\": 4220, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5860334755717507e-32, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 4265, \"end\": 4271, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\", \"score\": 0.9999999539577413, \"rank\": 4.60421121918797e-08, \"text\": \"Louvre\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\", \"Q33506\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\"}, {\"begin\": 4324, \"end\": 4341, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5113616592227155e-27, \"text\": \"Leonardo da Vinci\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}, {\"begin\": 4344, \"end\": 4353, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mona_Lisa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.79726197322948e-24, \"text\": \"Mona Lisa\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mona_Lisa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mona_Lisa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"France's La Marseillaise anthem rang out as the parade passed by the Grand Palais, before the show paid tribute to women who made French history, including former minister Simone Veil.\", \"from\": 4383, \"to\": 4567, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4383, \"end\": 4389, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5012365867739817e-13, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 4392, \"end\": 4407, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_Marseillaise\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.7112378371078005e-59, \"text\": \"La Marseillaise\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_Marseillaise\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_Marseillaise\"}, {\"begin\": 4513, \"end\": 4527, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French history\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_France\"}, {\"begin\": 4555, \"end\": 4566, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Veil\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Simone Veil\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Veil\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Veil\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At the start of the parade, applause erupted for the Greek boat - the first delegation, by tradition - and there were even bigger cheers for the boat that followed, carrying the refugees' team.\", \"from\": 4571, \"to\": 4764, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4624, \"end\": 4629, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"score\": 0.9646043596574289, \"rank\": 0.03654034461413412, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The French, US, and Ukrainian delegations also got loud cheers.\", \"from\": 4765, \"to\": 4828, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4769, \"end\": 4775, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9953359198909087, \"rank\": 0.004627841915488241, \"